report yet.
</pre>


## Secretary's Report

<pre>
OFTC has held an election.

Peter Palfrader is the new chair of OFTC and they have voted to remain an
associated project of SPI.

Other than that, no specific mail received to secretary@
</pre>

SPI congratulates Peter on his election and am sure SPI will continue to enjoy
working with OFTC.


## Outstanding Minutes


__Current status:__
All outstanding sets of minutes have been completed, and will be presented to
the board for approval at the next meeting.


## Report from Joshua D. Drake

I have been in contact with CentOS and Foresight Linux about possible SPI
inclusion.

Haskell contacted me directly via CosmicRay about the same possibility.

I have it on my TODO to start the financial provider review after PostgreSQL
Conference. The PostgreSQL Conference is already past expectations, so thank
you to SPI from PostgreSQL for helping us with this.

And lastly, I have a meeting with Software Freedom Law Center


## Membership Committee report

We will be moving forward with the membership expiry as per the charter.
Members should expect mail shortly regarding this.


## EU wide Debian trademark

Neil McGovern has had a chat with the DPL about the Europe wide trademark. He
will be approaching an eu based solicitor to help with this.


